### CSS Overflow

**overflow** controls what happens when content is too big for its container.

---

### Values

| Value | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `visible` | Content overflows box (default) |
| `hidden` | Content is clipped |
| `scroll` | Scrollbars always shown |
| `auto` | Scrollbars only when needed |
| `clip` | Like hidden, no scrolling |

---

### Overflow X and Y

```css
overflow-x: hidden;  /* Horizontal */
overflow-y: scroll;  /* Vertical */
overflow: hidden scroll; /* x | y shorthand */
```

---

### Overflow: Visible (Default)

```css
.container {
  width: 200px;
  height: 100px;
  overflow: visible; /* Content spills out */
}
```

---

### Overflow: Hidden

```css
.container {
  width: 200px;
  height: 100px;
  overflow: hidden; /* Extra content hidden */
}
```

Use with `border-radius` and `white-space: nowrap`.

---

### Overflow: Scroll

```css
.container {
  width: 200px;
  height: 100px;
  overflow: scroll; /* Always show scrollbars */
}
```

---

### Overflow: Auto

```css
.container {
  width: 200px;
  height: 100px;
  overflow: auto; /* Scrollbars only when needed */
}
```

---

### Text Overflow

```css
.text {
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis; /* Shows ... */
}
```

---

### Layout Applications

```css
/* Truncate text */
.truncate {
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
}

/* Prevent horizontal scroll */
body {
  overflow-x: hidden;
}

/* Scrollable sidebar */
.sidebar {
  height: 100vh;
  overflow-y: auto;
}

/* Clip image to rounded corners */
.card img {
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

> **Key Point:** `overflow: hidden` clips child content to parent boundaries, which is required for `border-radius` to clip corners properly.
